body_html: You could run it under sudo dtruss to see where it's trying to look for the dylib. Also, I've had to disable SIP (system integrity protection) for it to work, although that had extra dyld: warning messages in error log

body: You could run it under `sudo dtruss` to see where it's trying to look for the `dylib`. Also, I've had to disable SIP (system integrity protection) for it to work, although that had extra `dyld: warning` messages in error log
